Hi Ben,

Cantera uses the thermodynamic data written into the cti file to calculate the equilibrium constant:

Kp = exp(-delta_G_rxn/RT)) 

Kc = Kp*(product reference activity for each species raised to negative net stoichiometric coefficient)

and then uses this in conjunction with the forward rate constant to find the reverse rate:

Kc = k_fwd/k_rev

I&#39;m not sure which environment you&#39;re using for Cantera, but if you&#39;re looking for printouts of this data, there is a matlab function for the equilibrium constant (equil_Kc.m).  You can compute the forward and reverse rates in Matlab (using the functions rop_f.m & rop_r.m, stoich_r.m & stoich_p.m, and the product of moleFractions.m & molarDensity.m), though it takes just a little bit of coding, since there&#39;s no explicit function in matlab for this.

Hope this helps.

Best,
Steven


