            Hi folks,



I would like to write out the kinetic data of some reactions in a gas 

object. Does anyone know how I can get the pre-exponential frequency 

factor (A), pre-temperature index (n) and the activation energy of a 

reaction (Ea)?



In chemkin format, a reversable reaction has an equilibrium constant 

explicitly written just after the reaction string. In cti format, it 

looks like only the forward rate data are written. It does seem the 

reverse rates are also considered. My question is how does the code 

know the equilibrium constant or the reverse rate data?



Will appreciate any ideas on these questions.



Regards,

Ben Akih.














